Solitary colonic metastasis from renal-cell carcinoma 17 years after nephrectomy. Report of a case.
 Late recurrence of renal-cell carcinoma can present many years after nephrectomy.
 To the best of our knowledge, we are reporting the first known case of solitary metastatic renal-cell carcinoma to the colon occurring 17 years after nephrectomy.
